OL,6,FWhilst high-risk births took place in
OL,7,Fprior to the closure of the Stranraer
OL,8,Funit in 2018, some believe that if
OL,9,Fmaternity services returned to the
OL,10,Ftown staff would be better able to
OL,11,Fdeal with emergencies.
OL,13,FChantice Gibb was 19 weeks pregnant
OL,14,Fwhen she lost her baby in August 2022.
OL,15,FAfter experiencing pain she went to
OL,16,Fthe Emergency department in Stranraer,
OL,17,Fand was told to make her own way to
OL,18,FDumfries.
